From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kandelo <noreply@kandelo.invalid>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Support the isolated Kandelo bottle publisher

Kandelo's bottle publisher gives Formula evaluation root-owned, read-only
Homebrew source and trust state. Homebrew normally requires its repository to
be writable and persists a redundant per-item trust entry for every fully
qualified install, even when the containing tap is already trusted. Both
behaviors reject the publisher's intentionally immutable state before a
Formula can run.

The publisher also preinstalls reviewed dependencies before asking Homebrew to
build the selected Formula with `--ignore-dependencies`. That flag must prevent
Homebrew from recursively installing native packages into the target Cellar,
but the build child currently interprets it by dropping every dependency from
Superenv. Direct build tools such as WABT and Binaryen then disappear from the
Formula PATH even though their sealed proxy kegs are installed.

Homebrew on Linux also injects native sandbox dependencies such as Bubblewrap
into every Formula. Those host dependencies must remain available to native
Homebrew, but recording them in a Kandelo target bottle would make guest
Homebrew treat Linux executables as WebAssembly runtime dependencies.

Exclude only the Homebrew repository from the preinstall writability diagnostic
and skip automatic per-item persistence when the tap already grants the same
authority. When the isolated publisher supplies its protected static plan,
populate the build child's environment with only the matching direct native
build dependencies. Its schema distinguishes literal Formula dependencies from
statically allowlisted Requirements. Validate each evaluated Requirement's
class, Formula identity, sentinel executable, and tags against the sealed plan,
then reconstruct only those matching Formulae as build-only Superenv inputs.
Do not recursively expand them. Every selected dependency must already be
present as a proxy keg, so a missing proxy still fails closed.
For a Requirement also tagged `:test`, validate that its sealed proxy contains
the planned sentinel and expose only that proxy's standard tool and metadata
paths to Homebrew's Formula test process.
Use that same protected plan to suppress Linux global dependencies for the
identified Kandelo target and every Formula in its exact immutable target taps
while Homebrew derives the recursive target receipt. Formulae from other taps
and the separate native Homebrew prefix retain normal Linux dependency
resolution.
While that plan is active, also prevent `brew test` from automatically pouring
Bubblewrap into the target Cellar. A usable host Bubblewrap can still be used,
but an unavailable sandbox cannot bypass the publisher's reviewed native plan.
The publisher retains an embedded receipt for Kandelo's static VFS composer,
so make same-environment retries insensitive to tap-only commits with Homebrew's
upstream GNU tar flags.
Remove only the tap Git head from a fresh copy of the temporary archived receipt
and restore the exact installed receipt after bottling. Normalize the archive
file time to the stable source time used by Homebrew's tar and gzip paths.
Every other required Homebrew path remains subject to the normal writability
check, and explicit `brew trust` operations still use the normal mutation path and fail
against an immutable publisher store.

This patch is applied only to the publisher's temporary Homebrew overlay. Guest
Homebrew keeps its normal repository, trust, and dependency behavior.
---
 Library/Homebrew/build.rb                   | 31 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 Library/Homebrew/dev-cmd/bottle.rb          | 12 ++++++++++++
 Library/Homebrew/diagnostic.rb              |  1 +
 Library/Homebrew/extend/os/linux/formula.rb |  4 ++++
 Library/Homebrew/extend/os/linux/sandbox.rb |  4 +++-
 Library/Homebrew/kandelo_publisher.rb       | 225 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 Library/Homebrew/test.rb                    |  2 ++
 Library/Homebrew/trust.rb                   |  1 +
 8 files changed, 278 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Library/Homebrew/build.rb b/Library/Homebrew/build.rb
index be833176c0..c2c07f5bcf 100644
--- a/Library/Homebrew/build.rb
+++ b/Library/Homebrew/build.rb
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@ old_trap = trap("INT") { exit! 130 }

 require_relative "global"
 require "build_options"
+require "kandelo_publisher"
 require "keg"
 require "extend/ENV"
 require "fcntl"
@@ -43,12 +44,40 @@ class Build
     @deps = T.let([], T::Array[Dependency])
     @reqs = T.let(Requirements.new, Requirements)

-    return if args.ignore_dependencies?
+    if args.ignore_dependencies?
+      @deps = publisher_build_dependencies if args.build_bottle?
+      return
+    end

     @deps = expand_deps
     @reqs = expand_reqs
   end

+  sig { returns(T::Array[Dependency]) }
+  def publisher_build_dependencies
+    plan = KandeloPublisher.dependency_plan(formula)
+    return [] if plan.nil?
+
+    target_tap_prefixes = plan.fetch("target_taps").map { |tap| "#{tap.fetch("tap_name")}/" }
+    direct_native_formula_dependencies = formula.deps.select do |dependency|
+      dependency.build? && !dependency.implicit? &&
+        target_tap_prefixes.none? { |prefix| dependency.name.start_with?(prefix) }
+    end
+    native_requirement_dependencies =
+      KandeloPublisher.evaluated_native_requirements(formula, plan).map do |requirement|
+        Dependency.new(requirement.fetch("formula"), [:build])
+      end
+    direct_native_build_dependencies =
+      direct_native_formula_dependencies + native_requirement_dependencies
+    expected_names = plan.fetch("build")
+    actual_names = direct_native_build_dependencies.map(&:name).sort
+    if actual_names != expected_names
+      raise "Kandelo publisher dependency plan differs from direct native build dependencies"
+    end
+
+    direct_native_build_dependencies.sort_by(&:name)
+  end
+
   sig { params(dependent: Formula).returns(BuildOptions) }
   def effective_build_options_for(dependent)
     args  = dependent.build.used_options
